-width=\"2\"/><ellipse cx=\"36\" cy=\"68\" rx=\"27\" ry=\"10\" fill=\"#85c1e9\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><ellipse cx=\"36\" cy=\"24\" rx=\"27\" ry=\"10\" fill=\"#d6eaf8\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","o":["Cube","Sphere","Cylinder","Pyramid"],"a":2,"e":"Cylinder.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does a square have?<svg width=\"82\" height=\"82\" viewBox=\"0 0 82 82\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><rect x=\"11\" y=\"11\" width=\"60\" height=\"60\" fill=\"#fde8d8\" stroke=\"#e67e22\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"41\" y1=\"4\" x2=\"41\" y2=\"78\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/><line x1=\"4\" y1=\"41\" x2=\"78\" y2=\"41\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/><line x1=\"7\" y1=\"7\" x2=\"75\" y2=\"75\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/><line x1=\"75\" y1=\"7\" x2=\"7\" y2=\"75\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/></svg>","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":3,"e":"Square=4 lines.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does a circle have?<svg width=\"68\" height=\"68\" viewBox=\"0 0 68 68\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><line x1=\"65.0\" y1=\"34.0\" x2=\"3.0\" y2=\"34.0\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke-dasharray=\"4,3\" opacity=\"0.7\"/><line x1=\"55.9\" y1=\"55.9\" x2=\"12.1\" y2=\"12.1\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke-dasharray=\"4,3\" opacity=\"0.7\"/><line x1=\"34.0\" y1=\"65.0\" x2=\"34.0\" y2=\"3.0\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke-dasharray=\"4,3\" opacity=\"0.7\"/><line x1=\"12.1\" y1=\"55.9\" x2=\"55.9\" y2=\"12.1\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke-dasharray=\"4,3\" opacity=\"0.7\"/><circle cx=\"34\" cy=\"34\" r=\"29\" fill=\"#dff0f8\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/><text x=\"34\" y=\"39\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"11\" fill=\"#2980b9\" font-weight=\"bold\">∞</text></svg>","o":["1","4","8","Unlimited"],"a":3,"e":"Unlimited.","d":"h"},{"t":"Does the letter Z have a line of symmetry?<svg width=\"54\" height=\"64\" viewBox=\"0 0 54 64\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 4px\"><text x=\"27\" y=\"54\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"48\" font-weight=\"bold\" font-family=\"Arial,sans-serif\" fill=\"#5d3a8e\">Z</text><circle cx=\"43\" cy=\"12\" r=\"9\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"36\" y1=\"5\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"19\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","o":["Yes","No"],"a":1,"e":"Z has NO line of symmetry.","d":"h"},{"t":"Does the letter A have a line of symmetry?<svg width=\"54\" height=\"64\" viewBox=\"0 0 54 64\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 4px\"><text x=\"27\" y=\"54\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"48\" font-weight=\"bold\" font-family=\"Arial,sans-serif\" fill=\"#5d3a8e\">A</text><line x1=\"27\" y1=\"2\" x2=\"27\" y2=\"62\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/></svg>","o":["Yes, vertical","Yes, horizontal","No","Yes, diagonal"],"a":0,"e":"Vertical line through A.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does a rectangle have?<svg width=\"108\" height=\"66\" viewBox=\"0 0 108 66\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><rect x=\"7\" y=\"10\" width=\"94\" height=\"46\" fill=\"#fde8d8\" stroke=\"#e67e22\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"54\" y1=\"4\" x2=\"54\" y2=\"62\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/><line x1=\"2\" y1=\"33\" x2=\"106\" y2=\"33\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/></svg>","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":1,"e":"2 lines: horizontal and vertical.","d":"h"},{"t":"What does the word symmetry mean?","o":["4+ sides","Both halves match when folded","Always a circle","No corners"],"a":1,"e":"Fold: both halves match=symmetry.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does an equilateral triangle have?<svg width=\"82\" height=\"76\" viewBox=\"0 0 82 76\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><polygon points=\"41,4 6,72 76,72\" fill=\"#fde8d8\" stroke=\"#e67e22\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"41\" y1=\"2\" x2=\"41\" y2=\"74\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/></svg>","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":2,"e":"3 lines.","d":"h"},{"t":"Does the letter B have a line of symmetry?<svg width=\"54\" height=\"64\" viewBox=\"0 0 54 64\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 4px\"><text x=\"27\" y=\"54\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"48\" font-weight=\"bold\" font-family=\"Arial,sans-serif\" fill=\"#5d3a8e\">B</text><line x1=\"2\" y1=\"32\" x2=\"52\" y2=\"32\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/></svg>","o":["Yes, vertical","Yes, horizontal","No","Yes, diagonal"],"a":1,"e":"Horizontal line through B.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which shape has NO symmetry?<svg width=\"78\" height=\"74\" viewBox=\"0 0 78 74\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><polygon points=\"10,66 70,66 20,8\" fill=\"#fce4ec\" stroke=\"#c0392b\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><circle cx=\"64\" cy=\"14\" r=\"10\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"57\" y1=\"7\" x2=\"71\" y2=\"21\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","o":["Square","Circle","Rectangle","Scalene triangle"],"a":3,"e":"Scalene triangle (all sides different) has no symmetry.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does the letter H have?<svg width=\"54\" height=\"64\" viewBox=\"0 0 54 64\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 4px\"><text x=\"27\" y=\"54\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"48\" font-weight=\"bold\" font-family=\"Arial,sans-serif\" fill=\"#5d3a8e\">H</text><line x1=\"27\" y1=\"2\" x2=\"27\" y2=\"62\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/><line x1=\"2\" y1=\"32\" x2=\"52\" y2=\"32\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/></svg>","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":1,"e":"H has both vertical and horizontal=2.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does a 5-pointed star have?<svg width=\"80\" height=\"80\" viewBox=\"0 0 80 80\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><line x1=\"40.0\" y1=\"1.0\" x2=\"40.0\" y2=\"79.0\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke-dasharray=\"4,3\" opacity=\"0.7\"/><line x1=\"77.1\" y1=\"27.9\" x2=\"2.9\" y2=\"52.1\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke-dasharray=\"4,3\" opacity=\"0.7\"/><line x1=\"62.9\" y1=\"71.6\" x2=\"17.1\" y2=\"8.4\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke-dasharray=\"4,3\" opacity=\"0.7\"/><line x1=\"17.1\" y1=\"71.6\" x2=\"62.9\" y2=\"8.4\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke-dasharray=\"4,3\" opacity=\"0.7\"/><line x1=\"2.9\" y1=\"27.9\" x2=\"77.1\" y2=\"52.1\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke-dasharray=\"4,3\" opacity=\"0.7\"/><polygon points=\"40.0,4.0 48.8,27.9 74.2,28.9 54.3,44.6 61.2,69.1 40.0,55.0 18.8,69.1 25.7,44.6 5.8,28.9 31.2,27.9\" fill=\"#f9e79f\" stroke=\"#f39c12\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","o":["3","4","5","6"],"a":2,"e":"5-pointed star=5 lines.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does a regular hexagon have?<svg width=\"70\" height=\"70\" viewBox=\"0 0 70 70\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><polygon points=\"35.0,6.0 60.1,20.5 60.1,49.5 35.0,64.0 9.9,49.5 9.9,20.5\" fill=\"#fde8d8\" stroke=\"#e67e22\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/></svg>","o":["4","5","6","8"],"a":2,"e":"Regular hexagon=6 lines.","d":"h"},{"t":"A line of symmetry divides a shape into two parts that are?","o":["3 equal parts","2 matching halves","4 equal parts","Unequal parts"],"a":1,"e":"2 matching (mirror) halves.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does the letter O have?<svg width=\"54\" height=\"64\" viewBox=\"0 0 54 64\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 4px\"><text x=\"27\" y=\"54\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"48\" font-weight=\"bold\" font-family=\"Arial,sans-serif\" fill=\"#5d3a8e\">O</text><line x1=\"27\" y1=\"2\" x2=\"27\" y2=\"62\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/></svg>","o":["1","2","4","Unlimited"],"a":3,"e":"O is like a circle=unlimited.","d":"h"},{"t":"Does the letter M have a line of symmetry?<svg width=\"54\" height=\"64\" viewBox=\"0 0 54 64\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 4px\"><text x=\"27\" y=\"54\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"48\" font-weight=\"bold\" font-family=\"Arial,sans-serif\" fill=\"#5d3a8e\">M</text><line x1=\"27\" y1=\"2\" x2=\"27\" y2=\"62\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/></svg>","o":["Yes, vertical","Yes, horizontal","No","Yes, diagonal"],"a":0,"e":"Vertical line through M.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which shape has more lines of symmetry: a square or a rectangle?<svg width=\"62\" height=\"62\" viewBox=\"0 0 62 62\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><line x1=\"31.0\" y1=\"3.0\" x2=\"31.0\" y2=\"59.0\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/><line x1=\"50.8\" y1=\"11.2\" x2=\"11.2\" y2=\"50.8\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/><line x1=\"59.0\" y1=\"31.0\" x2=\"3.0\" y2=\"31.0\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/><line x1=\"50.8\" y1=\"50.8\" x2=\"11.2\" y2=\"11.2\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/><polygon points=\"31.0,6.0 56.0,31.0 31.0,56.0 6.0,31.0\" fill=\"#e8d5f5\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/></svg><svg width=\"90\" height=\"58\" viewBox=\"0 0 90 58\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><rect x=\"7\" y=\"10\" width=\"96\" height=\"48\" fill=\"#fde8d8\" stroke=\"#e67e22\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"55\" y1=\"4\" x2=\"55\" y2=\"64\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/><line x1=\"2\" y1=\"34\" x2=\"108\" y2=\"34\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/></svg>","o":["Rectangle","Square","Equal","Neither"],"a":1,"e":"Square=4, Rectangle=2.","d":"h"},{"t":"Butterfly has which type of symmetry?<svg width=\"100\" height=\"84\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 84\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><ellipse cx=\"25\" cy=\"28\" rx=\"23\" ry=\"17\" fill=\"#d7bde2\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2\" transform=\"rotate(-18 25 28)\"/><ellipse cx=\"75\" cy=\"28\" rx=\"23\" ry=\"17\" fill=\"#d7bde2\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2\" transform=\"rotate(18 75 28)\"/><ellipse cx=\"22\" cy=\"57\" rx=\"17\" ry=\"12\" fill=\"#c39bd3\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2\" transform=\"rotate(12 22 57)\"/><ellipse cx=\"78\" cy=\"57\" rx=\"17\" ry=\"12\" fill=\"#c39bd3\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2\" transform=\"rotate(-12 78 57)\"/><ellipse cx=\"50\" cy=\"42\" rx=\"5\" ry=\"27\" fill=\"#6c3483\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"16\" x2=\"39\" y2=\"4\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"16\" x2=\"61\" y2=\"4\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"39\" cy=\"4\" r=\"2.5\" fill=\"#8e44ad\"/><circle cx=\"61\" cy=\"4\" r=\"2.5\" fill=\"#8e44ad\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"1\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"82\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/></svg>","o":["Rotational","Vertical line","Horizontal line","No symmetry"],"a":1,"e":"Butterfly has 1 vertical line of symmetry.","d":"h"},{"t":"Does the letter S have a line of symmetry?<svg width=\"54\" height=\"64\" viewBox=\"0 0 54 64\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 4px\"><text x=\"27\" y=\"54\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"48\" font-weight=\"bold\" font-family=\"Arial,sans-serif\" fill=\"#5d3a8e\">S</text><circle cx=\"43\" cy=\"12\" r=\"9\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"36\" y1=\"5\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"19\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","o":["Yes, vertical","Yes, horizontal","No","Yes, diagonal"],"a":2,"e":"S has no line of symmetry (it is NOT symmetric by fold).","d":"h"},{"t":"Which letter has NO symmetry?<svg width=\"54\" height=\"64\" viewBox=\"0 0 54 64\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 4px\"><text x=\"27\" y=\"54\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"48\" font-weight=\"bold\" font-family=\"Arial,sans-serif\" fill=\"#5d3a8e\">F</text><circle cx=\"43\" cy=\"12\" r=\"9\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"36\" y1=\"5\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"19\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","o":["A","H","M","F"],"a":3,"e":"F has no line of symmetry.","d":"h"},{"t":"Can a shape have more than one line of symmetry?","o":["No","Yes","Only circles","Only squares"],"a":1,"e":"Yes! Square has 4, circle has unlimited.","d":"e"},{"t":"Snowflake typically has how many lines of symmetry?<svg width=\"82\" height=\"82\" viewBox=\"0 0 82 82\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><line x1=\"41.0\" y1=\"3.0\" x2=\"41.0\" y2=\"79.0\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1\" stroke-dasharray=\"3,2\" opacity=\"0.5\"/><line x1=\"60.0\" y1=\"8.1\" x2=\"22.0\" y2=\"73.9\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1\" stroke-dasharray=\"3,2\" opacity=\"0.5\"/><line x1=\"73.9\" y1=\"22.0\" x2=\"8.1\" y2=\"60.0\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1\" stroke-dasharray=\"3,2\" opacity=\"0.5\"/><line x1=\"79.0\" y1=\"41.0\" x2=\"3.0\" y2=\"41.0\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1\" stroke-dasharray=\"3,2\" opacity=\"0.5\"/><line x1=\"73.9\" y1=\"60.0\" x2=\"8.1\" y2=\"22.0\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1\" stroke-dasharray=\"3,2\" opacity=\"0.5\"/><line x1=\"60.0\" y1=\"73.9\" x2=\"22.0\" y2=\"8.1\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"1\" stroke-dasharray=\"3,2\" opacity=\"0.5\"/><line x1=\"41\" y1=\"41\" x2=\"41.0\" y2=\"5.0\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/><line x1=\"41.0\" y1=\"21.2\" x2=\"34.8\" y2=\"12.4\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"41.0\" y1=\"21.2\" x2=\"47.2\" y2=\"12.4\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"41\" y1=\"41\" x2=\"72.2\" y2=\"23.0\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/><line x1=\"58.1\" y1=\"31.1\" x2=\"62.7\" y2=\"21.3\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"58.1\" y1=\"31.1\" x2=\"68.9\" y2=\"32.0\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"41\" y1=\"41\" x2=\"72.2\" y2=\"59.0\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/><line x1=\"58.1\" y1=\"50.9\" x2=\"68.9\" y2=\"50.0\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"58.1\" y1=\"50.9\" x2=\"62.7\" y2=\"60.7\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"41\" y1=\"41\" x2=\"41.0\" y2=\"77.0\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/><line x1=\"41.0\" y1=\"60.8\" x2=\"47.2\" y2=\"69.6\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"41.0\" y1=\"60.8\" x2=\"34.8\" y2=\"69.6\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"41\" y1=\"41\" x2=\"9.8\" y2=\"59.0\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/><line x1=\"23.9\" y1=\"50.9\" x2=\"19.3\" y2=\"60.7\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"23.9\" y1=\"50.9\" x2=\"13.1\" y2=\"50.0\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"41\" y1=\"41\" x2=\"9.8\" y2=\"23.0\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/><line x1=\"23.9\" y1=\"31.1\" x2=\"13.1\" y2=\"32.0\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"23.9\" y1=\"31.1\" x2=\"19.3\" y2=\"21.3\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"41\" cy=\"41\" r=\"4\" fill=\"#2980b9\"/></svg>","o":["2","3","6","12"],"a":2,"e":"Snowflakes have 6 lines of symmetry.","d":"h"},{"t":"If you fold a shape along its line of symmetry, what happens to the two halves?","o":["Are different","Match exactly","Change shape","Disappear"],"a":1,"e":"Both halves match exactly.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does the letter X have?<svg width=\"54\" height=\"64\" viewBox=\"0 0 54 64\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 4px\"><text x=\"27\" y=\"54\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"48\" font-weight=\"bold\" font-family=\"Arial,sans-serif\" fill=\"#5d3a8e\">X</text><line x1=\"27\" y1=\"2\" x2=\"27\" y2=\"62\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/><line x1=\"2\" y1=\"32\" x2=\"52\" y2=\"32\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/></svg>","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":1,"e":"X has 2 lines of symmetry: vertical and horizontal.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does a regular pentagon have?<svg width=\"70\" height=\"70\" viewBox=\"0 0 70 70\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><polygon points=\"35.0,6.0 62.6,26.0 52.0,58.5 18.0,58.5 7.4,26.0\" fill=\"#fde8d8\" stroke=\"#e67e22\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/></svg>","o":["3","4","5","6"],"a":2,"e":"Regular pentagon=5 lines.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which number has vertical symmetry?","o":["3","5","8","9"],"a":2,"e":"8 has a vertical line of symmetry.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does a rhombus have?<svg width=\"78\" height=\"78\" viewBox=\"0 0 78 78\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><polygon points=\"39,5 73,39 39,73 5,39\" fill=\"#e8d5f5\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"39\" y1=\"2\" x2=\"39\" y2=\"76\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/><line x1=\"2\" y1=\"39\" x2=\"76\" y2=\"39\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/></svg>","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":1,"e":"Rhombus=2 lines (diagonals).","d":"h"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does a right triangle have?<svg width=\"78\" height=\"74\" viewBox=\"0 0 78 74\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><polygon points=\"8,66 8,8 70,66\" fill=\"#fce4ec\" stroke=\"#c0392b\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><rect x=\"8\" y=\"52\" width=\"14\" height=\"14\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#c0392b\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"64\" cy=\"14\" r=\"10\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"57\" y1=\"7\" x2=\"71\" y2=\"21\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","o":["0","1","2","3"],"a":0,"e":"Right triangle=0 lines of symmetry.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does an arrow pointing to the right have?","o":["0","1","2","3"],"a":1,"e":"Horizontal arrow=1 horizontal line.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which shapes always have at least 1 line of symmetry?","o":["Scalene triangle","Right triangle","Isosceles triangle","All triangles"],"a":2,"e":"Isosceles triangle has 1 line of symmetry.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does a heart shape have?<svg width=\"78\" height=\"72\" viewBox=\"0 0 78 72\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><path d=\"M39,22 Q39,6 22,6 Q8,6 8,26 Q8,50 39,68 Q70,50 70,26 Q70,6 56,6 Q39,6 39,22 Z\" fill=\"#fad4d4\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"39\" y1=\"2\" x2=\"39\" y2=\"70\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,3\"/></svg>","o":["0","1","2","3"],"a":1,"e":"Heart has 1 vertical line of symmetry.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many sides does a hexagon have?<svg width=\"70\" height=\"70\" viewBox=\"0 0 70 70\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><polygon points=\"35.0,6.0 60.1,20.5 60.1,49.5 35.0,64.0 9.9,49.5 9.9,20.5\" fill=\"#e8d5f5\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/></svg>","o":["4","5","6","8"],"a":2,"e":"6.","d":"h"},{"t":"Circle sides?","o":["0","1","2","3"],"a":0,"e":"0.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many faces does a cube have?<svg width=\"88\" height=\"78\" viewBox=\"0 0 88 78\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><polygon points=\"44,4 77,22 44,40 11,22\" fill=\"#d7bde2\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><polygon points=\"11,22 44,40 44,68 11,50\" fill=\"#a569bd\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><polygon points=\"44,40 77,22 77,50 44,68\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","o":["4","5","6","8"],"a":2,"e":"6.","d":"h"},{"t":"A soup can is shaped like which 3D shape?<svg width=\"72\" height=\"82\" viewBox=\"0 0 72 82\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><rect x=\"9\" y=\"24\" width=\"54\" height=\"44\" fill=\"#aed6f1\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><ellipse cx=\"36\" cy=\"68\" rx=\"27\" ry=\"10\" fill=\"#85c1e9\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><ellipse cx=\"36\" cy=\"24\" rx=\"27\" ry=\"10\" fill=\"#d6eaf8\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","o":["Cube","Sphere","Cone","Cylinder"],"a":3,"e":"Cylinder.","d":"h"},{"t":"An ice cream cone is shaped like which 3D shape?<svg width=\"72\" height=\"82\" viewBox=\"0 0 72 82\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><polygon points=\"36,4 7,70 65,70\" fill=\"#f9e79f\" stroke=\"#f39c12\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><ellipse cx=\"36\" cy=\"70\" rx=\"29\" ry=\"9\" fill=\"#f7dc6f\" stroke=\"#f39c12\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","o":["Cube","Sphere","Cone","Cylinder"],"a":2,"e":"Cone.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which shape has all 4 sides the same length?","o":["Rectangle","Rhombus","Square","Trapezoid"],"a":2,"e":"Square.","d":"m"},{"t":"Rectangle symmetry?","o":["Yes","No","Sometimes","Never"],"a":0,"e":"Yes, 2 lines.","d":"e"},{"t":"A ball is shaped like which 3D shape?<svg width=\"72\" height=\"72\" viewBox=\"0 0 72 72\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><circle cx=\"36\" cy=\"36\" r=\"30\" fill=\"#d7bde2\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><ellipse cx=\"36\" cy=\"36\" rx=\"30\" ry=\"10\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#8e44ad\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" opacity=\"0.5\"/><ellipse cx=\"36\" cy=\"36\" rx=\"10\" ry=\"30\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#8e44ad\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" opacity=\"0.5\"/></svg>","o":["Cube","Sphere","Cone","Pyramid"],"a":1,"e":"Sphere.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many sides does a pentagon have?<svg width=\"70\" height=\"70\" viewBox=\"0 0 70 70\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><polygon points=\"35.0,6.0 62.6,26.0 52.0,58.5 18.0,58.5 7.4,26.0\" fill=\"#e8d5f5\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2.5\"/></svg>","o":["4","5","6","7"],"a":1,"e":"5.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many edges does a cube have?<svg width=\"88\" height=\"78\" viewBox=\"0 0 88 78\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 5px\"><polygon points=\"44,4 77,22 44,40 11,22\" fill=\"#d7bde2\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><polygon points=\"11,22 44,40 44,68 11,50\" fill=\"#a569bd\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><polygon points=\"44,40 77,22 77,50 44,68\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" stroke=\"#6c3483\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","o":["8","10","12","14"],"a":2,"e":"12.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many sides does a pentagon have?","o":["4","5","6","8"],"a":1,"e":"A pentagon has 5 sides. 'Penta' means five.","d":"e"},{"t":"What 3D shape does a dice look like?","o":["Sphere","Cylinder","Cube","Cone"],"a":2,"e":"A dice is shaped like a cube -- it has 6 square faces.","d":"e"},{"t":"Does a square have a line of symmetry?","o":["Yes","No","Only big squares","Only small squares"],"a":0,"e":"Yes! A square has 4 lines of symmetry. You can fold it in half many ways and both sides match.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many corners does a hexagon have?","o":["4","5","6","8"],"a":2,"e":"A hexagon has 6 corners (vertices) -- the same number as its sides.","d":"e"},{"t":"What shape is a globe?","o":["Cube","Cone","Cylinder","Sphere"],"a":3,"e":"A globe is shaped like a sphere -- it is round in every direction.","d":"e"},{"t":"If you fold a heart shape in half down the middle, do the two sides match?","o":["Yes","No","Only sometimes","Only big hearts"],"a":0,"e":"Yes! A heart has a line of symmetry down the middle. Both halves are mirror images.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many sides does an octagon have?","o":["6","7","8","10"],"a":2,"e":"An octagon has 8 sides. Think of a stop sign!","d":"e"},{"t":"How many flat faces does a cone have?","o":["0","1","2","3"],"a":1,"e":"A cone has 1 flat face (the circular base) and 1 curved surface going up to the point.","d":"e"},{"t":"Two squares placed side by side make a ___.","o":["Triangle","Rectangle","Circle","Pentagon"],"a":1,"e":"Two squares side by side create a rectangle that is twice as long as it is tall.","d":"e"},{"t":"What shape is round with no corners?","o":["Square","Triangle","Circle","Hexagon"],"a":2,"e":"A circle is round with no corners and no straight sides.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many edges does a cube have?","o":["6","8","10","12"],"a":3,"e":"A cube has 12 edges -- the lines where two faces meet.","d":"e"},{"t":"Does the letter X have a line of symmetry?","o":["Yes","No","Only capital X","Only in some fonts"],"a":0,"e":"Yes! The letter X has lines of symmetry -- both vertical and horizontal.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the name of a shape with 3 sides?","o":["Square","Triangle","Pentagon","Hexagon"],"a":1,"e":"A triangle has 3 sides. 'Tri' means three.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which 3D shape can roll but NOT slide?","o":["Cube","Sphere","Rectangular prism","Triangular prism"],"a":1,"e":"A sphere can only roll because it has no flat faces to slide on.","d":"e"},{"t":"What shapes do you get if you cut a rectangle from top to bottom down the middle?","o":["2 triangles","2 smaller rectangles","2 circles","2 hexagons"],"a":1,"e":"Cutting a rectangle straight down the middle gives 2 smaller rectangles.","d":"e"},{"t":"What 3D shape does a can of beans look like?","o":["Cube","Sphere","Cone","Cylinder"],"a":3,"e":"A can of beans is shaped like a cylinder -- 2 flat circle faces and a curved surface.","d":"e"},{"t":"A square has how many equal sides?","o":["2","3","4","0"],"a":2,"e":"A square has 4 equal sides -- all the same length.","d":"m"},{"t":"Does a circle have any corners?","o":["Yes, 1","Yes, many","No, 0 corners","Yes, 4"],"a":2,"e":"A circle has 0 corners (vertices). It is completely smooth and curved.","d":"e"},{"t":"A shape has 4 sides and 4 right angles, but NOT all sides are equal. What is it?","o":["Square","Non-square rectangle","Triangle","Hexagon"],"a":1,"e":"A non-square rectangle has 4 sides and 4 right angles, but 2 sides are longer than the other 2.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many more faces does a cube have than a triangular prism?","o":["0","1","2","3"],"a":1,"e":"A cube has 6 faces and a triangular prism has 5. 6 - 5 = 1 more face.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which has more lines of symmetry: an equilateral triangle or a square?","o":["Equilateral triangle (3 vs 4)","Square (4 vs 3)","They are equal","Neither has any"],"a":1,"e":"A square has 4 lines of symmetry. An equilateral triangle has 3. The square has more.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many more sides does an octagon have than a pentagon?","o":["2","3","4","5"],"a":1,"e":"An octagon has 8 sides. A pentagon has 5 sides. 8 - 5 = 3 more sides.","d":"e"},{"t":"What 2D shape do you see if you trace the face of a cylinder?","o":["Square","Triangle","Rectangle","Circle"],"a":3,"e":"The flat face of a cylinder is a circle. Tracing it gives you a circle.","d":"m"},{"t":"You cut a square from one corner to the opposite corner. What shapes do you get?","o":["2 squares","2 rectangles","2 triangles","1 triangle and 1 rectangle"],"a":2,"e":"A diagonal cut through a square creates 2 identical right triangles.","d":"e"},{"t":"Maria says a quadrilateral always has to be a rectangle. Is she right?","o":["Yes, all quadrilaterals are rectangles","No -- a quadrilateral is any shape with 4 sides","Yes, if it has 4 corners","No -- quadrilaterals have 5 sides"],"a":1,"e":"A quadrilateral is ANY shape with 4 sides. Rectangles are quadrilaterals, but so are trapezoids, rhombuses, and other 4-sided shapes.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which 3D shape has 2 triangular faces and 3 rectangular faces?","o":["Cube","Rectangular prism","Triangular prism","Cylinder"],"a":2,"e":"A triangular prism has 2 triangular end faces and 3 rectangular side faces = 5 faces total.","d":"m"},{"t":"A non-square rectangle has ___ lines of symmetry.","o":["0","1","2","4"],"a":2,"e":"A non-square rectangle has 2 lines of symmetry: one horizontal and one vertical through the center.","d":"m"},{"t":"Sort from fewest sides to most: octagon, triangle, pentagon.","o":["Triangle, pentagon, octagon","Pentagon, triangle, octagon","Octagon, pentagon, triangle","Triangle, octagon, pentagon"],"a":0,"e":"Triangle = 3 sides, pentagon = 5, octagon = 8. Order: triangle, pentagon, octagon.","d":"m"},{"t":"A ___ can slide but NOT roll because all its faces are flat.","o":["Sphere","Cylinder","Cone","Cube"],"a":3,"e":"A cube has only flat faces (no curved surfaces), so it can slide but never roll.","d":"e"},{"t":"If 2 identical triangles share one full side, how many sides does the new shape have?","o":["3","4","5","6"],"a":1,"e":"Each triangle has 3 sides (6 total). The shared side is hidden inside, removing 2 edges. 6 - 2 = 4 sides.","d":"m"},{"t":"I am a polygon. I have 1 more side than a pentagon and 2 fewer sides than an octagon. What am I?","o":["Square","Hexagon","Heptagon","Triangle"],"a":1,"e":"Pentagon = 5 sides. 5 + 1 = 6. Octagon = 8 sides. 8 - 2 = 6. A hexagon has 6 sides.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many vertices does a rectangular prism have?","o":["4","6","8","12"],"a":2,"e":"A rectangular prism has 8 vertices (corners): 4 on top and 4 on the bottom.","d":"e"},{"t":"Does the letter T have a line of symmetry?","o":["Yes -- 1 vertical line","Yes -- 2 lines","No lines of symmetry","Yes -- 1 horizontal line"],"a":0,"e":"The capital letter T has 1 line of symmetry: a vertical line down the center. Left and right halves match.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is different about a cube and a rectangular prism?","o":["A cube has 6 faces but a rectangular prism does not","A cube has all square faces; a rectangular prism can have rectangular faces","A rectangular prism has more vertices","A cube can roll but a rectangular prism cannot"],"a":1,"e":"Both have 6 faces, 8 vertices, and 12 edges. The difference: a cube's faces are ALL squares, while a rectangular prism can have rectangular faces.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does a regular hexagon have?","o":["3","4","6","8"],"a":2,"e":"A regular hexagon has 6 lines of symmetry -- one from each vertex to the opposite vertex, and one through each pair of opposite sides.","d":"e"},{"t":"Amy put 4 squares in a 2x2 grid. What shape did she make?","o":["A rectangle","A bigger square","A triangle","A pentagon"],"a":1,"e":"Four identical squares in a 2x2 arrangement make one bigger square.","d":"m"},{"t":"A cone has ___ flat face(s) and ___ vertex (vertices).","o":["0 faces, 0 vertices","1 face, 1 vertex","2 faces, 0 vertices","1 face, 2 vertices"],"a":1,"e":"A cone has 1 flat circular face (the base) and 1 vertex (the point at the top).","d":"m"},{"t":"Which shape does NOT belong: hexagon, pentagon, circle, octagon?","o":["Hexagon","Pentagon","Circle","Octagon"],"a":2,"e":"Circle does not belong. The hexagon, pentagon, and octagon are all polygons (straight sides). A circle is not a polygon.","d":"e"},{"t":"Kai says all rectangles are quadrilaterals and all quadrilaterals are polygons. Is he correct?","o":["Yes, both statements are true","First is true, second is false","First is false, second is true","Both are false"],"a":0,"e":"Kai is correct on both! Rectangles have 4 sides so they are quadrilaterals. Quadrilaterals have straight sides so they are polygons.","d":"m"},{"t":"Leo glues 2 cubes together on one face. He says the new shape has 12 faces. What mistake did he make?","o":["He is actually correct","The 2 hidden faces should be subtracted: 12 - 2 = 10","He forgot to add more faces: it has 14","Cubes have 8 faces each, so it is 16"],"a":1,"e":"Each cube has 6 faces (12 total). But the 2 faces glued together are hidden inside. 12 - 2 = 10 visible faces.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many lines of symmetry does a regular hexagon have? How does that compare to a regular pentagon?","o":["Hexagon has 6, pentagon has 5 -- hexagon has 1 more","Both have 6","Hexagon has 4, pentagon has 5 -- pentagon has more","Hexagon has 3, pentagon has 5"],"a":0,"e":"A regular hexagon has 6 lines of symmetry. A regular pentagon has 5. The hexagon has 1 more.","d":"m"},{"t":"Tom says a cylinder has 2 edges. Sara says it has 0 edges because edges must be straight. Who is correct in standard 2nd grade geometry?","o":["Tom -- the circular rims are edges","Sara -- edges must be straight","Both are correct","Neither -- it has 1 edge"],"a":0,"e":"In standard elementary geometry, a cylinder has 2 edges -- the circular rims where each flat face meets the curved surface. Tom is correct.","d":"m"},{"t":"You remove a small triangle from one corner of a large square. How many sides does the remaining shape have?","o":["3","4","5","6"],"a":2,"e":"Removing a triangle from one corner replaces that corner with a new edge. The square had 4 sides; losing 1 corner and gaining 1 new side = 5 sides total.","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape has half as many lines of symmetry as a regular hexagon. What could it be?","o":["Equilateral triangle","Square","Non-square rectangle","Regular pentagon"],"a":0,"e":"A regular hexagon has 6 lines of symmetry. Half of 6 = 3. An equilateral triangle has exactly 3 lines of symmetry.","d":"m"},{"t":"Emma says a triangular prism has more edges than a cube. Is she correct?","o":["Yes -- 12 vs 9","No -- cube has 12 edges, triangular prism has 9","They are equal at 12 each","Neither has edges"],"a":1,"e":"A cube has 12 edges and a triangular prism has 9 edges. The cube has MORE, so Emma is incorrect.","d":"m"},{"t":"You fold a regular hexagon along all its lines of symmetry and unfold it. The fold lines divide it into how many equal triangles?","o":["3","6","8","12"],"a":3,"e":"A regular hexagon has 6 lines of symmetry. These lines divide it into 12 equal right triangles (each of the 6 equilateral triangles is split in half).","d":"m"},{"t":"A 3D shape has 0 faces, 0 edges, and 0 vertices. What must it be?","o":["Cube","Cylinder","Cone","Sphere"],"a":3,"e":"A sphere has 0 flat faces, 0 edges, and 0 vertices. It is completely curved.","d":"m"},{"t":"You compose a new shape by placing a triangle on top of a square (sharing the top side). Then you place another triangle on the bottom. How many sides does the new shape have?","o":["4","6","8","10"],"a":1,"e":"The square has 4 sides. Each triangle covers 1 square side and adds 2 new sides. So: 4 - 2 (covered) + 4 (new from triangles) = 6 sides. The shape looks like a diamond/hexagon.","d":"m"},{"t":"Rosa says if a shape has 4 equal sides, it MUST be a square. What shape proves her wrong?","o":["Rectangle","Rhombus (diamond)","Triangle","Pentagon"],"a":1,"e":"A rhombus has 4 equal sides but its angles are not all right angles. It is a diamond shape, not a square. Rosa is wrong.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many total vertices do a triangular prism and a rectangular prism have combined?","o":["12","14","16","18"],"a":1,"e":"Triangular prism = 6 vertices. Rectangular prism = 8 vertices. 6 + 8 = 14 vertices.","d":"e"},{"t":"Mia says if you cut a non-square rectangle diagonally, you get 2 identical triangles with 1 line of symmetry each. Is she fully correct?","o":["Yes, completely correct","The triangles are identical, but they have 0 lines of symmetry each","The triangles are not identical","She is completely wrong"],"a":1,"e":"The 2 triangles ARE identical (congruent). But each is a scalene right triangle with no line of symmetry (the sides are all different lengths). Mia is wrong about symmetry.","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape has twice as many sides as a square. What is it?","o":["Pentagon","Hexagon","Octagon","Decagon"],"a":2,"e":"A square has 4 sides. Twice 4 = 8 sides. An octagon has 8 sides.","d":"m"},{"t":"You stack a cone on a cylinder and a sphere on the cone. How many total flat faces are visible from the outside?","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":0,"e":"The cylinder bottom is the only visible flat face. The cylinder top is hidden under the cone. The cone base is hidden too. The sphere has no flat faces. Total: 1.","d":"m"},{"t":"Ben arranges 5 identical squares in a plus sign (+) shape. How many sides does the outline of the plus sign have?","o":["8","10","12","20"],"a":2,"e":"A plus sign made of 5 squares has 12 outside edges. Count around the outside -- each arm has 3 exposed sides, and there are 4 arms: that accounts for all 12.","d":"m"},{"t":"Ava says a shape with 6 lines of symmetry must be a regular hexagon. Can you find a counterexample?","o":["She is correct -- only hexagons have 6 lines","A circle has even more than 6","A 12-pointed star could also have 6 lines","Both a circle and a regular 12-sided shape have more, but a Star of David has exactly 6"],"a":3,"e":"A circle has infinitely many lines, and some star shapes (like a Star of David) also have 6 lines of symmetry. So a regular hexagon is not the ONLY shape with 6 lines.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many more edges does a rectangular prism have than a cone?","o":["9","10","11","12"],"a":2,"e":"A rectangular prism has 12 edges. A cone has 1 edge (the circular rim). 12 - 1 = 11 more edges.","d":"e"},{"t":"Jake puts 2 equilateral triangles base-to-base to form a larger shape. What shape does he make, and how many lines of symmetry does it have?","o":["A square with 4 lines","A rhombus with 2 lines","A rectangle with 2 lines","A hexagon with 6 lines"],"a":1,"e":"Two equilateral triangles base-to-base make a rhombus (diamond). This rhombus has 2 lines of symmetry: one along the shared base and one connecting the two points.","d":"m"},{"t":"A regular polygon has N sides and N lines of symmetry. If N + N = 16, what polygon is it?","o":["Hexagon","Heptagon","Octagon","Decagon"],"a":2,"e":"N + N = 16, so 2N = 16, meaning N = 8. A regular polygon with 8 sides is an octagon. It also has 8 lines of symmetry.","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle has two sides of 5 inches and two sides of 3 inches. What is the total distance around it?","o":["16 inches","15 inches","8 inches","10 inches"],"a":0,"e":"Add all 4 sides: 5+3+5+3=16 inches all the way around!"},{"t":"A square has 4 corners (vertices). A triangle has 3 corners. How many corners in all?","o":["7","5","9","12"],"a":0,"e":"Add the vertices: 4+3=7 corners in all!"}]});
